Locators (ID, Name, LinkText, PartialLinkText, Class & Tag)
---------

We can identify various elements on the web using Locators
Locators are addresses that identify a web element uniquely within the page.

Locators -> [ID, Name, LinkText, PartialLinkText, Class & Tag]

Customized Locators -> [CSS Selector, Xpath]

CSS Selectors:
	Tag and ID
	Tag and Class
	Tag and Attribute
	Tag, Class and Attribute

Xpath:
	Absolute XPath
	Relative XPath



TagName - We cannot use TagName for finding a particular Webelement. TagName is used for identifing and locating group of webelements.
Class - Category of Element. Same kind of elements are having same values for class attribute (Dropdown, Input) Used to locate group of elements or multiple web elements


To calculate 'N' number of links or images in the particular page, we use this TagName and Class Locators 

<ul> tag represents - user list
<li> tag represenrs - list item


FindElement() - Return Single WebElement
FindElements() - Return Multiple WebElement

Scenario 1: Locator matching with single web element
findElement(loc) ----> Return Single web element - WebElement
findElements(loc) --->  Return Single web element - List<WebElement>

Scenario 2: Locator matching with multi web element
findElement(loc) ----> 	Return Single web element - WebElement [Return first element]
findElements(loc) --->  Return multi web element - List<WebElement>

Scenario 3: Locator not matching with any web element/s
findElement(loc) ----> 	Return "No such Element Exception"
findElements(loc) --->  Returns 0 . It will not throw any exception.


